WEBVTT

00:02.636 --> 00:04.203
<i>"LAST MAN STANDING"</i>

00:04.205 --> 00:05.637
<i>IS RECORDED IN FRONT OF</i>
<i>A LIVE STUDIO AUDIENCE.</i>

00:05.639 --> 00:07.373
JUST GOING AWAY
FOR THE WEEKEND, HONEY.

00:07.375 --> 00:08.974
DO YOU HAVE TO
PACK ALL YOUR ANVILS?

00:08.976 --> 00:11.844
MAN! A SUITE
AT THE FOUR SEASONS?

00:11.846 --> 00:14.546
THIS IS SOME ANNIVERSARY PRESENT
ED GOT YOU GUYS.

00:14.548 --> 00:16.849
HE KNOWS WHEN
MY BIRTHDAY IS, RIGHT?

00:16.851 --> 00:20.319
YOU KNOW THE BEST THING ABOUT
GOING TO VAIL DURING SKI SEASON?

00:20.321 --> 00:21.854
NO CROWDS.

00:22.857 --> 00:24.323
MANDY.
YES.

00:24.325 --> 00:26.658
HONEY, THERE IS A PAN OF ZITI
IN THE FRIDGE

00:26.660 --> 00:27.793
FOR DINNER
WHEN EVE GETS HOME --

00:27.795 --> 00:29.395
350 FOR AN HOUR.

00:29.397 --> 00:31.530
YOU DON'T HAVE TO MAKE US FOOD.
I KNOW HOW TO COOK.

00:31.532 --> 00:33.532
WHAT DOES "350" MEAN?

00:33.534 --> 00:37.636
THAT'S WHAT ZITI GETS PAID
PER HOUR, SO EAT FAST.

00:37.638 --> 00:39.838
WE GOT TO HUSTLE.
THEY SAY THE ROADS
ARE GETTING BAD.

00:39.840 --> 00:41.073
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

00:41.075 --> 00:42.041
AND PLEASE JUST REMEMBER
TO WALK MUFFIN

00:42.043 --> 00:43.242
SO HE CAN DO HIS BUSINESS.

00:43.244 --> 00:44.476
I THOUGHT
WE GOT HIM FIXED.

00:44.478 --> 00:46.011
THAT'S NOT
THE PART WE HAD FIXED.

00:46.013 --> 00:48.247
OH, MOM, THE WEBSITE SAYS
THAT THERE'S AN INDOOR POOL.

00:48.249 --> 00:50.149
IF YOU WANT,
YOU CAN BORROW THE BATHING SUIT

00:50.151 --> 00:51.550
I GOT FOR SPRING BREAK --

00:51.552 --> 00:53.252
YOU KNOW, IF YOU HAVE ROOM
FOR IT IN YOUR SUITCASE.

00:53.254 --> 00:55.387
[ Chuckling ] OH, YEAH,
I HAVE SEEN THAT BATHING SUIT,

00:55.389 --> 00:57.056
AND THERE IS ROOM FOR IT
IN MY<i> WALLET.</i>

00:58.159 --> 00:59.224
I WANT YOU TO TAKE CARE
OF YOUR SISTER.

00:59.226 --> 01:00.726
YOU'RE IN CHARGE
OF THE HOUSE.
[ SIGHS ]

01:00.728 --> 01:02.528
I KNOW YOU'RE OLD ENOUGH.
I DON'T NEED TO SAY THIS.

01:02.530 --> 01:04.830
BUT, UH, YEAH,
GOODBYE, HOUSE.

01:08.702 --> 01:10.569
WHEW.
THAT'S NOT MY POINT.

01:10.571 --> 01:14.106
MY POINT IS CLOSING THE HIGHWAY
IN COLORADO BECAUSE OF SNOW

01:14.108 --> 01:15.774
IS LIKE CLOSING CALIFORNIA

01:15.776 --> 01:18.243
BECAUSE THEY'RE WRONG
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

01:18.245 --> 01:20.879
WELL, I, FOR ONE, AM GLAD
THEY TURNED US BACK.

01:20.881 --> 01:23.949
I MEAN, WE SAW THREE CARS
SPIN OUT AND A TRUCK JACKKNIFE.

01:23.951 --> 01:25.951
I'M NOT SAYING
IT WASN'T EXCITING.
AW, JUST...

01:25.953 --> 01:28.053
WHY DOES OUR HOUSE
LOOK LIKE

01:28.055 --> 01:30.989
THE GREENROOM
OF "GOOD MORNING, DENVER"?

01:31.759 --> 01:33.592
HEY!

01:35.596 --> 01:38.097
HAPPY ANNIVERSARY!

01:39.867 --> 01:42.134
MANDY, YOU --
YOU THREW US A PARTY.

01:42.136 --> 01:45.571
[ Singsong voice ]
YOU BETTER BELIEVE IT.

01:45.573 --> 01:47.473
HOW DID YOU KNOW
WE WERE COMING BACK?

01:47.475 --> 01:49.041
OH, WAIT A MINUTE.
I GOT IT.

01:49.043 --> 01:51.310
YOU HEARD THAT THE FOUR SEASONS
BURNED DOWN.

01:51.312 --> 01:53.145
YES.

01:53.147 --> 01:55.280
I SAW THAT ON THE NEWS,
YOU GUYS.

01:55.282 --> 01:56.248
OH, MY GOD.

01:56.250 --> 01:57.816
AND MY FIRST THOUGHT WAS,

01:57.818 --> 01:59.485
"THIS IS TOTALLY GONNA WRECK
MOM AND DAD'S ANNIVERSARY."

01:59.487 --> 02:01.553
THEN I WAS LIKE,
"NOT ON MY WATCH."

02:01.555 --> 02:02.888
SO...

02:03.991 --> 02:06.658
...HAPPY ANNIVERSARY!

02:06.660 --> 02:09.261
THE FOUR SEASONS
DID NOT BURN DOWN.

02:09.263 --> 02:12.798
IT'S AN ANNIVERSARY
MIRACLE!

02:12.800 --> 02:14.299
SO YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
A LITTLE PARTY, HUH?

02:14.301 --> 02:15.734
NO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:15.736 --> 02:17.436
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]
I'M GONNA GET THAT.

02:17.438 --> 02:18.837
PROBABLY JUST SOME LOST PEOPLE
WHO ARE CARRYING PRETZELS.

02:18.839 --> 02:20.672
PLEASE MOVE OUT OF THE WAY.
MOVE IT.

02:20.674 --> 02:21.640
OKAY.

02:23.010 --> 02:23.976
HEY!
HEY!

02:23.978 --> 02:25.344
AND YOU BROUGHT BEER?

02:25.346 --> 02:26.778
YEAH,
IT'S FOR THE PARTY.

02:26.780 --> 02:28.247
OH, YOU'RE ONE OF THOSE
COOL DADS, HUH?

02:28.249 --> 02:30.082
[ LAUGHS MOCKINGLY ]
NO.

02:31.085 --> 02:32.618
AW, MANDY.
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

02:32.620 --> 02:33.685
I AM SO DISAPPOINTED.

02:33.687 --> 02:36.655
SO AM I.
WHAT IS FAT BASTARD ALE?

02:38.092 --> 02:41.193
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:44.832 --> 02:46.165
IT WAS JUST A PARTY.

02:46.167 --> 02:47.366
I DIDN'T THINK
IT WAS THAT BIG A DEAL.

02:47.368 --> 02:50.636
WITH UNDERAGE KIDS,
LIQUOR, AND MY GUNS?

02:50.638 --> 02:53.472
THIS IS HOW THE ALAMO
GOT STARTED.

02:53.474 --> 02:55.174
HEY, HEY, SOME KID
COULD'VE LEFT HERE DRUNK

02:55.176 --> 02:56.608
AND WRAPPED HIS CAR
AROUND A TREE.

02:56.610 --> 02:58.277
WE'D BE LIABLE FOR THAT.

02:58.279 --> 03:00.345
AND TO DO ALL THIS WITH YOUR
LITTLE SISTER IN THE HOUSE --

03:00.347 --> 03:01.513
MANDY, THE ONE THING
WE ASKED YOU TO DO

03:01.515 --> 03:02.814
WAS TO TAKE CARE OF EVE.

03:02.816 --> 03:04.716
YOU ASKED ME TO DO
A LOT OF THINGS.

03:04.718 --> 03:06.051
I DID<i> SOME</i> OF THEM.

03:06.053 --> 03:07.886
I GAVE THE DOG ZITI
EXACTLY AT 3:50.

03:11.292 --> 03:12.524
UH...WHAT HAPPENED?

03:12.526 --> 03:13.892
I THOUGHT
YOU GUYS WERE GOING TO VAIL.

03:13.894 --> 03:17.529
THE HOTEL BURNED DOWN --
BUT NOT REALLY.

03:17.531 --> 03:18.897
THEY CLOSED I-70.

03:18.899 --> 03:20.966
LOOK, DID YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT MANDY'S PARTY?

03:20.968 --> 03:22.000
WHAT?

03:22.002 --> 03:23.235
[ Chuckling ]
YEAH, RIGHT.

03:23.237 --> 03:25.871
LIKE I WOULD INVITE HER
TO MY PARTY.

03:25.873 --> 03:27.206
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

03:27.208 --> 03:28.640
IF THOSE ARE
MORE OF YOUR FRIENDS,

03:28.642 --> 03:30.642
LET'S JUST HOPE THEY HAVE
A BEER THAT I RECOGNIZE.

03:32.079 --> 03:32.978
[ Chuckling ] HEY.

03:32.980 --> 03:34.246
DETECTIVE MIKE BAXTER.

03:34.248 --> 03:36.114
I HAVE A FEW QUESTIONS
FOR YOU ALL.

03:39.253 --> 03:41.019
I WANT YOU TO GO TEXT
ALL YOUR FRIENDS

03:41.021 --> 03:42.521
AND TELL THEM
THE PARTY'S OFF

03:42.523 --> 03:44.590
AND THEN COME BACK DOWN HERE
AND CLEAN UP THIS MESS.

03:44.592 --> 03:45.724
OKAY.
AND WATCH MUFFIN.

03:45.726 --> 03:46.992
IF HE STARTS DOING CIRCLES,

03:46.994 --> 03:48.794
THAT ZITI'S LOOKING
FOR A WAY OUT.

03:50.064 --> 03:52.497
YOU KNOW WHAT? THANK GOD
THAT HIGHWAY GOT SNOWED OUT.

03:52.499 --> 03:54.166
'CAUSE WE'RE HERE
YELLING AT OUR KIDS

03:54.168 --> 03:56.168
RATHER THAN BEING RUBBED DOWN
BY SOME CROATIAN WOMAN

03:56.170 --> 03:57.369
IN A FOUR-STAR HOTEL.

03:57.371 --> 03:59.771
DID YOU BUY
ALL THAT STUFF WITH EVE?

03:59.773 --> 04:01.840
SHE KNEW ABOUT THIS PARTY.

04:01.842 --> 04:04.643
I GUESS WE CAN'T COUNT ON EVE
TO TELL ON HER SISTERS ANYMORE.

04:06.113 --> 04:07.779
RIGHT.

04:07.781 --> 04:10.415
WE'LL HAVE TO ADOPT A NEW KID
TO SPY ON THEM.

04:11.585 --> 04:15.354
I WONDER WHAT RUSSIAN BABIES
GO FOR THESE DAYS.

04:15.356 --> 04:17.222
YOU KNOW,
MANDY'S GOT TO BE PUNISHED.

04:17.224 --> 04:19.591
SHE'S NOT GONNA BE 21
FOR ANOTHER TWO WHOLE MONTHS.

04:19.593 --> 04:22.094
WHAT IS THE RUSH
TO START DRINKING, ANYWAY?

04:24.865 --> 04:26.298
BOY.

04:26.300 --> 04:28.166
NO WONDER
THIS BASTARD GOT FAT.

04:30.904 --> 04:32.871
SO, THIS WILL BE
A LOW WALL

04:32.873 --> 04:35.440
BETWEEN THE RESTAURANT
AND THE SHOPPING AREA.
I GOTCHA. OKAY.

04:35.442 --> 04:37.876
WE WILL LET THE CUSTOMERS
SEE HOW GOOD THE FOOD LOOKS,

04:37.878 --> 04:39.311
AND THAT WILL
DRAW THEM IN.

04:39.313 --> 04:41.113
WHAT IF THE FOOD
LOOKS TERRIBLE?

04:41.115 --> 04:43.215
WON'T THAT HAVE
THE OPPOSITE EFFECT?

04:43.217 --> 04:45.651
UH...LET ME SEE.
HOW CAN I FIX THAT?

04:45.653 --> 04:47.619
OH, I KNOW --
THE FOOD<i> WON'T</i> LOOK TERRIBLE.

04:47.621 --> 04:49.087
ALL RIGHT.

04:49.089 --> 04:51.456
WELL, I'M JUST HERE
TO ASK THE HARD QUESTIONS.

04:51.458 --> 04:54.092
THAT'S MY JOB.
BUT THEY
HAVE TO BE REASONABLE.

04:54.094 --> 04:56.061
WHAT IF A METEOR
HIT THE RESTAURANT?

04:56.063 --> 04:57.596
WELL, THEN YOUR LOW WALLS

04:57.598 --> 04:59.998
WILL OFFER
NO PROTECTION WHATSOEVER.

05:01.302 --> 05:03.568
I'M JUST BUSTING YOUR CHOPS,
KRISTIN --

05:03.570 --> 05:05.170
ASSUMING
GIRLS HAVE CHOPS.

05:05.172 --> 05:07.673
YOUR DAD WAS RIGHT
TO BRING YOU IN ON THIS.

05:07.675 --> 05:08.674
YOU'RE TOP-NOTCH.

05:08.676 --> 05:11.143
THANK YOU.

05:11.145 --> 05:12.911
SPEAKING OF MY DAD...
[CHUCKLES]

05:12.913 --> 05:15.314
THAT WAS QUITE THE EXTRAVAGANT
ANNIVERSARY PRESENT

05:15.316 --> 05:16.315
YOU GOT MY PARENTS.

05:16.317 --> 05:17.582
WELL, AFTER 10 YEARS,

05:17.584 --> 05:19.918
IT'S SAFE TO SPEND
BIG BUCKS ON A GIFT.

05:19.920 --> 05:21.987
BEFORE THAT,
YOU GIVE CHEAP STUFF

05:21.989 --> 05:24.022
THEY CAN SPLIT UP
WHEN<i> THEY</i> DO.

05:25.159 --> 05:26.858
YOU REALIZE
I'M GETTING MARRIED IN A MONTH?

05:26.860 --> 05:28.360
NUMBERS DON'T LIE.

05:28.362 --> 05:30.662
BEFORE THE 10-YEAR ANNIVERSARY,
YOU KNOW,

05:30.664 --> 05:32.764
50% OF MARRIAGES
END IN DIVORCE.

05:32.766 --> 05:35.133
ACTUALLY,
I HEARD THAT IS A MYTH.

05:35.135 --> 05:38.036
NO,<i> BIGFOOT</i> IS A MYTH,
AND IF IT'S NOT,

05:38.038 --> 05:41.373
THERE ARE 10 BIGFOOTS
AND 5 HAVE BEEN DIVORCED.

05:41.375 --> 05:44.710
SO, YOU'RE -- YOU'RE SAYING
THAT MY MARRIAGE TO RYAN

05:44.712 --> 05:47.212
HAS A 50% CHANCE
OF LASTING 10 YEARS?

05:47.214 --> 05:49.114
NO, I'M SAYING
THAT YOUR GIFT

05:49.116 --> 05:51.750
WILL BE SOMETHING
EASILY DIVISIBLE BY TWO.

05:55.656 --> 05:57.222
[ VIDEO GAME BEEPING ]

05:57.224 --> 05:58.690
HELLO.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.025
HEY.
WHAT'S YOUR SCAM?

06:00.027 --> 06:01.026
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

06:01.028 --> 06:02.561
I'M NOT UP TO ANYTHING.

06:02.563 --> 06:05.063
I'M JUST SITTING HERE
SLINGING BIRDS AT PIGS.

06:05.065 --> 06:07.366
[ GROANS ] COME ON.
YOU MUST WANT SOMETHING FROM ME.

06:07.368 --> 06:09.134
OTHERWISE,
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE PRETENDED

06:09.136 --> 06:11.536
IT WAS<i> YOUR</i> PARTY
WHEN IT WAS<i> MINE.</i>

06:11.538 --> 06:15.040
YOU...
YOU WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND.

06:15.042 --> 06:17.175
YOU'RE GONNA GET IN TROUBLE
COVERING FOR ME LIKE THIS.

06:17.177 --> 06:18.510
MOM AND DAD
ARE REALLY PISSED.

06:18.512 --> 06:20.245
YEAH,
BUT NOT SURPRISED.

06:20.247 --> 06:23.215
YOU KNOW, THEY EXPECT
STUFF LIKE THIS FROM ME.

06:23.217 --> 06:24.816
YOU, ON THE OTHER HAND,

06:24.818 --> 06:27.919
YOU'RE THE LITTLE GOOSE
THAT POOPS THE GOLDEN EGGS.

06:29.156 --> 06:30.555
A GOOSE DOES NOT POOP EGGS.

06:30.557 --> 06:31.590
REALLY?

06:31.592 --> 06:33.058
AFTER MY NICE GESTURE,

06:33.060 --> 06:34.359
YOU'RE GONNA GET
ALL BIOLOGY ON ME HERE?

06:34.361 --> 06:36.661
AND HONESTLY,
SINCE WHEN DO YOU CARE?

06:36.663 --> 06:39.564
YOU'VE RATTED ME OUT TO THEM
LIKE A MILLION TIMES.

06:39.566 --> 06:41.099
YEAH, AND THIS WAS
A PERFECT CHANCE

06:41.101 --> 06:42.567
FOR YOU
TO GET BACK AT ME.

06:42.569 --> 06:44.569
WELL, MAYBE
I'M JUST THE BETTER SISTER.

06:46.407 --> 06:48.206
WE ALL KNOW
THAT'S NOT IT.

06:48.208 --> 06:50.709
LOOK, KRISTIN'S
COVERED FOR ME BEFORE,

06:50.711 --> 06:52.077
I'VE COVERED FOR HER.

06:52.079 --> 06:54.813
IT'S JUST WHAT SISTERS
ARE SUPPOSED TO DO.

06:56.183 --> 06:57.349
WELL, THANKS.

06:57.351 --> 06:59.551
YOU'RE WELCOME.

06:59.553 --> 07:01.253
IF KRISTIN LISTENED
TO ME,

07:01.255 --> 07:03.955
MOM AND DAD STILL WOULDN'T KNOW
SHE HAS A KID.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.963
LOOKS LIKE
OUR ANNIVERSARY DINNER'S

07:11.965 --> 07:14.132
GONNA BE COLD ZITI
AND CELERY STICKS.

07:14.134 --> 07:16.701
ALL RIGHT, I'LL TAKE THE ZITI
AND A ROLAIDS.

07:16.703 --> 07:18.770
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
ABOUT MANDY? YOU KNOW?

07:18.772 --> 07:21.306
I MEAN, HER -- HER PUNISHMENT
HAS TO BE SOMETHING BIG.

07:21.308 --> 07:22.574
A BOAT.

07:22.576 --> 07:24.543
SHE'D HATE IT
IF I GOT A BOAT OUT OF THIS.

07:24.545 --> 07:26.311
WHAT ABOUT
HER SPRING-BREAK TRIP?

07:26.313 --> 07:27.979
I THINK
WE SHOULD CANCEL THAT.

07:27.981 --> 07:29.714
OH,
THAT'S KIND OF CRUEL.

07:29.716 --> 07:32.818
I WAS LOOKING FORWARD
TO HER BEING GONE FOR A WHILE.

07:32.820 --> 07:34.986
IF WE CAN'T TRUST HER JUDGMENT
WHEN SHE'S HOME,

07:34.988 --> 07:36.788
WHO KNOWS
WHAT SHE'S GONNA DO IN CANCúN

07:36.790 --> 07:40.058
IN A WALLET-SIZE BIKINI?

07:40.060 --> 07:41.927
YOU KNOW,
IF I HAD A BOAT,

07:41.929 --> 07:44.729
I COULD, YOU KNOW,
WATCH HER FROM THE BOAT.

07:44.731 --> 07:46.565
BABY, COME ON.
SHE'S ALMOST 21.

07:46.567 --> 07:48.667
I REALLY DON'T SEE
WHAT THE PROBLEM IS HERE.
[ SIGHS ]

07:48.669 --> 07:51.069
WELL, WHEN I TRIED TO PULL
SOMETHING LIKE THIS,

07:51.071 --> 07:53.405
MY PARENTS CAME DOWN ON ME
LIKE A TON OF BRICKS.

07:53.407 --> 07:54.573
OH, BOY.

07:54.575 --> 07:56.174
IS THIS
THAT UGLY, UGLY STORY

07:56.176 --> 07:58.143
ABOUT WHEN YOU GOT
YOUR FIRST A-MINUS?

07:58.145 --> 07:59.511
NO, NO, NO, NO

07:59.513 --> 08:01.112
I NEVER TOLD THIS
TO ANYONE BEFORE,

08:01.114 --> 08:02.981
BUT MY PARENTS USED TO TAKE
APRIL AND ME

08:02.983 --> 08:04.249
TO CEDAR POINT
EVERY YEAR.

08:04.251 --> 08:05.984
UH-HUH. RIGHT.

08:05.986 --> 08:07.686
AND WHEN I WAS 17,
I HAD SUMMER SCHOOL,

08:07.688 --> 08:09.020
SO I STAYED HOME.

08:09.022 --> 08:10.789
I MEAN, I DIDN'T REALLY NEED
SUMMER SCHOOL.

08:10.791 --> 08:12.824
I JUST WANTED TO GET
A JUMP ON THE NEXT SEMESTER.

08:14.595 --> 08:17.529
I CAN SEE WHY YOU NEVER TOLD
ANYONE THIS STORY.

08:17.531 --> 08:20.365
JUST WAIT.
THIS JET IS ABOUT TO TAKE OFF.
OKAY.

08:20.367 --> 08:23.268
OKAY, SO, THE FIRST NIGHT
I HAVE THE HOUSE TO MYSELF,

08:23.270 --> 08:26.271
I INVITE A FEW FRIENDS OVER
FOR A "DANCE FEVER" PARTY.

08:26.273 --> 08:28.006
I MEAN, YOU HAD THOSE, RIGHT?
"DANCE FEVER"?

08:28.008 --> 08:28.840
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]

08:28.842 --> 08:30.308
[ LAUGHS ]
YEAH.

08:30.310 --> 08:33.512
SO, MY GIRLFRIENDS COME OVER
TO DANCE.

08:33.514 --> 08:37.015
OH, AND WE DANCED GOOD,
MIKE.

08:37.017 --> 08:39.818
AND THEN SUDDENLY,
THE DOOR FLIES OPEN,

08:39.820 --> 08:42.654
AND THERE THEY ARE --
MY PARENTS.

08:42.656 --> 08:43.688
YEAH.

08:43.690 --> 08:45.624
MY SISTER RATTED ME OUT.

08:45.626 --> 08:48.627
THEY GROUNDED ME
FOR TWO WHOLE MONTHS.

08:48.629 --> 08:50.862
AND YOU WERE DANCING
SO GOOD.

08:50.864 --> 08:52.330
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

08:52.332 --> 08:53.732
[ Sighing ] YEAH.

08:53.734 --> 08:55.000
YOU KNOW WHAT?

08:55.002 --> 08:57.035
WORSE THAN BEING GROUNDED,

08:57.037 --> 08:59.004
MY PARENTS SAID THEY WERE
DISAPPOINTED IN ME,

08:59.006 --> 09:00.972
AND SOME PEOPLE SAY
THAT'S THE WORST PUNISHMENT

09:00.974 --> 09:02.407
YOU CAN GET
WHEN YOU'RE A KID.

09:02.409 --> 09:04.809
THOSE PEOPLE HAVE NEVER BEEN
SMACKED IN THE HEAD

09:04.811 --> 09:06.044
WITH A BROWN WING TIP.

09:07.881 --> 09:09.381
HEY, DAD,
I WAS JUST TALKING ABOUT YOU.
OH, HI.

09:10.751 --> 09:11.983
HI, BUD.
HOW ARE YOU?
HELLO, MICHAEL.

09:11.985 --> 09:13.852
VANESSA.

09:13.854 --> 09:18.089
I NEEDED TO COME BY
ON THIS HAPPY OCCASION.

09:18.091 --> 09:19.558
OH, THAT'S SWEET,

09:19.560 --> 09:21.426
BUT OUR ANNIVERSARY CELEBRATION
HIT A LITTLE GLITCH.

09:21.428 --> 09:23.028
IS IT YOUR ANNIVERSARY?

09:23.030 --> 09:23.862
YES, DAD.

09:23.864 --> 09:25.263
27 YEARS AGO TODAY,

09:25.265 --> 09:28.266
YOU GOT INTO A FISTFIGHT
AT OUR RECEPTION.

09:28.268 --> 09:31.770
AS I RECALL,
THAT JACKASS HAD IT COMING.

09:31.772 --> 09:33.004
WHAT THE HELL
WAS HIS NAME?

09:33.006 --> 09:35.206
REVEREND TURNER.

09:35.208 --> 09:37.442
SO, WHAT IS
YOUR HAPPY OCCASION, BUD?

09:37.444 --> 09:39.511
YOUR BROTHER JIMMY'S
IN TOWN.

09:39.513 --> 09:42.080
HE'S TAKING ME OUT
FOR A BIG, FAT STEAK.

09:42.082 --> 09:45.617
BUT I NEEDED A NECKTIE,
SO HERE I AM.

09:45.619 --> 09:46.952
YOU DON'T HAVE A NECKTIE?

09:46.954 --> 09:48.219
NOT ANYMORE.

09:48.221 --> 09:49.854
WHEN I OPENED
THE WEED SHOP,

09:49.856 --> 09:52.123
I DECIDED I SHOULD START
DRESSING MORE GROOVY.

09:52.125 --> 09:53.792
[ LAUGHS ]

09:53.794 --> 09:55.260
SO, NUMBER 27?

09:55.262 --> 09:56.761
Vanessa: YEAH.

09:56.763 --> 09:59.698
THAT'S THE...
DORITO ANNIVERSARY?

09:59.700 --> 10:02.467
OH, NO, NO, NO.
THIS ISN'T FOR US.

10:02.469 --> 10:03.969
MANDY TRIED
TO SNEAK IN A PARTY

10:03.971 --> 10:05.570
BECAUSE SHE THOUGHT
WE WERE GONE.

10:05.572 --> 10:06.471
THAT'S HILARIOUS.

10:06.473 --> 10:07.606
NO.

10:07.608 --> 10:09.207
ACTUALLY,
IT'S NOT HILARIOUS, DAD.

10:09.209 --> 10:12.444
IT NEVER IS WHEN THE CHICKENS
COME HOME TO ROOST,

10:12.446 --> 10:13.979
AND<i> YOU'RE</i> THE ROOST.

10:13.981 --> 10:15.480
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

10:15.482 --> 10:17.582
WHEN MIKE WAS A KID,
HE WAS A PIECE OF WORK.

10:17.584 --> 10:19.150
HE WAS ALWAYS
GETTING IN TROUBLE.

10:19.152 --> 10:21.586
I WASN'T ALWAYS IN TROUBLE.
ALWAYS IN TROUBLE.

10:21.588 --> 10:23.822
I'LL BET HE NEVER TOLD YOU
ABOUT THE TIME

10:23.824 --> 10:25.657
HE STOLE MY TRUCK
AND WRECKED IT.

10:25.659 --> 10:27.993
YOU STOLE
YOUR DAD'S TRUCK?
YES.

10:27.995 --> 10:30.662
I'M AN INFAMOUS TRUCK THIEF.
DO YOU WANT YOUR RING BACK?

10:31.898 --> 10:33.498
HE ROLLED IT
INTO A CREEK BED.

10:33.500 --> 10:35.467
I KICKED YOUR ASS PRETTY GOOD
FOR THAT.

10:35.469 --> 10:37.168
THAT'S A GREAT STORY
YOU CAN TELL THE GEEZERS

10:37.170 --> 10:38.169
WHEN I PUT YOU IN A HOME.

10:39.506 --> 10:41.006
I HAD TO BE HARD ON YOU.

10:41.008 --> 10:42.507
JIMMY IDOLIZED YOU.

10:42.509 --> 10:44.809
I DIDN'T WANT HIM
GOING DOWN THE SAME PATH.

10:44.811 --> 10:46.745
I NEVER
HAD TO BEAT THAT KID.

10:46.747 --> 10:49.080
THAT'S HOW MY DAD'S GENERATION
PLAYED FAVORITES.

10:49.082 --> 10:51.349
"BEAT THIS ONE,
BUT LET'S NOT BEAT THAT ONE."

10:52.519 --> 10:53.985
LISTEN, POP, I GOT THE TIE

10:53.987 --> 10:54.919
I WAS GONNA WEAR
FOR OUR ANNIVERSARY DINNER.

10:54.921 --> 10:56.621
WHAT DO YOU THINK OF THAT?

10:56.623 --> 10:58.990
IT'S A LITTLE FLAMBOYANT,
DON'T YOU THINK, MICHAEL?

10:58.992 --> 11:02.794
YEAH, IT'S OUT THERE.
IT'S TWO COLORS.

11:02.796 --> 11:04.596
I KNOW WHERE
YOU KEEP YOUR TIES.

11:04.598 --> 11:08.199
I WANT A NECKTIE,
NOT A NEW LIFESTYLE.

11:11.872 --> 11:13.605
LET'S GO WITH
THE BIGGER LETTERING

11:13.607 --> 11:14.873
ON THE MENUS,
ALL RIGHT?

11:14.875 --> 11:16.541
A LOT OF OUR CUSTOMERS
ARE OLDER,

11:16.543 --> 11:18.109
AND THEY
DON'T SEE VERY WELL.

11:18.111 --> 11:19.911
AND YET
YOU SELL THEM GUNS.

11:22.282 --> 11:23.448
CAN I ASK YOU
A PERSONAL QUESTION?

11:23.450 --> 11:24.649
GO AHEAD.

11:24.651 --> 11:26.084
HOW MANY TIMES
HAVE YOU BEEN MARRIED?

11:27.354 --> 11:29.487
UH...
I'M SORRY, WHAT?

11:29.489 --> 11:31.956
FOUR.

11:31.958 --> 11:34.059
AND NONE OF THEM
LASTED 10 YEARS?

11:34.061 --> 11:38.363
MY MARRIAGE RECORD READS
LIKE MY GOLF SCORES --

11:38.365 --> 11:40.331
A 6, A 7, A 9, AN 8.

11:40.333 --> 11:42.233
WHY DO YOU THINK THAT IS?

11:42.235 --> 11:45.904
I'VE BEEN TOLD I DON'T
ROTATE MY HIPS VERY WELL.

11:47.641 --> 11:49.674
I HOPE
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT GOLF.

11:49.676 --> 11:51.009
[ SIGHS ]

11:51.011 --> 11:53.044
MARRIAGE IS
VERY, VERY COMPLICATED,

11:53.046 --> 11:54.479
AND AFFAIRS DON'T HELP.

11:54.481 --> 11:56.514
MARRIAGE COUNSELORS
TEND TO FROWN ON THOSE.

11:56.516 --> 11:57.749
NOT OURS.

11:57.751 --> 11:59.984
HE HAD ONE
WITH WIFE NUMBER TWO.

11:59.986 --> 12:02.654
THIS IS NOT
WHAT I WANT TO HEAR, MR. ALZATE.

12:02.656 --> 12:04.189
I'M ABOUT TO GET MARRIED,

12:04.191 --> 12:07.225
AND THERE'S NO WAY FOR ME
TO KNOW IF IT'S GONNA LAST.

12:07.227 --> 12:09.661
IT -- IT'S SCARY.

12:09.663 --> 12:13.665
KRISTIN,<i> EVERYBODY</i> FEELS LIKE
THAT BEFORE THEY GET MARRIED.

12:13.667 --> 12:14.866
I GUESS THAT'S TRUE.

12:14.868 --> 12:18.603
I FELT LIKE THAT
FOUR TIMES.

12:18.605 --> 12:20.171
AND I WAS RIGHT
EVERY TIME.

12:24.544 --> 12:26.344
ALL RIGHT,
I WANT TO BRING MANDY DOWN,

12:26.346 --> 12:27.779
BUT WE HAVE TO AGREE
ON HER PUNISHMENT.
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

12:27.781 --> 12:29.247
HEY,
IF IT'S NOT TOO CRUEL,

12:29.249 --> 12:31.449
HAVE HER SIT THROUGH
THAT "DANCE FEVER" STORY.

12:32.619 --> 12:34.919
JUST GOT TO BE HONEST --
THAT JET NEVER TOOK OFF.

12:37.290 --> 12:38.356
HEY, CAMMY.

12:38.358 --> 12:40.725
OH. MR. BAXTER.
YOU'RE HERE.

12:40.727 --> 12:44.062
YEAH, I'M HERE IN MY OWN HOME.
CRAZY WORLD, HUH?

12:44.064 --> 12:45.296
HEY, CAMMY.

12:45.298 --> 12:47.132
WHAT, UH --
WHAT DO YOU HAVE THERE?

12:47.134 --> 12:48.032
KARAOKE MACHINE?

12:48.034 --> 12:49.634
WHERE?

12:50.804 --> 12:53.104
IN THE BOX THAT SAYS
"KARAOKE MACHINE" ON IT.

12:53.106 --> 12:55.140
OH. [ LAUGHS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:55.142 --> 12:56.274
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I DO.

12:56.276 --> 12:57.542
[ Chuckling ] HEY.

12:57.544 --> 12:59.043
YOU BRINGING THAT
TO THE PARTY?

12:59.045 --> 13:00.745
PARTY?
NO, NO, NO.

13:00.747 --> 13:04.482
I-I JUST THOUGHT YOU GUYS
MIGHT WANT A K-KARAOKE MACHINE

13:04.484 --> 13:06.084
BECAUSE THEY'RE...

13:06.086 --> 13:08.186
FUN FOR THE WHOLE FAMILY.

13:09.556 --> 13:10.789
LOOK, CAMMY, YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN
A REALLY HONEST KID,

13:10.791 --> 13:12.423
AND I LIKE YOU BECAUSE --

13:12.425 --> 13:14.559
EVE ASKED ME TO BRING IT
FOR HER PARTY. I'M SORRY.

13:14.561 --> 13:15.894
EVE?
WAIT, EVE'S PARTY?

13:15.896 --> 13:17.262
I DON'T WANT
TO SAY ANYTHING ELSE

13:17.264 --> 13:18.596
IF IT'S GONNA
GET HER IN TROUBLE.

13:18.598 --> 13:20.064
EVE'S THE ONE
WHO'S THROWING THE PARTY?

13:20.066 --> 13:22.300
OH, GOD!
WHY WAS I BORN?!

13:23.069 --> 13:24.769
I-I SHOULD GO.

13:24.771 --> 13:26.571
LISTEN, BUT IT'S OKAY,
IT'S OKAY. CALM DOWN.

13:26.573 --> 13:28.239
ANYBODY WOULD'VE CAVED
UNDER THE TORTURE

13:28.241 --> 13:29.641
YOU JUST
PUT YOURSELF THROUGH.

13:34.014 --> 13:37.482
WELL, I CAN'T BELIEVE EVE
WOULD PULL SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

13:37.484 --> 13:39.083
YOU KNOW WHAT --
I CAN'T BELIEVE

13:39.085 --> 13:40.318
THAT MANDY WAS WILLING
TO TAKE THE RAP FOR THIS.

13:40.320 --> 13:42.086
IT SOUNDS LIKE
YOU ADMIRE HER FOR THAT.

13:42.088 --> 13:45.089
I DO. I TOLD HER TO TAKE CARE
OF HER SISTER, AND SHE DID.

13:45.091 --> 13:46.357
YEAH, BY LYING.

13:46.359 --> 13:48.193
I LIED FOR MY LITTLE BROTHER
ALL THE TIME.

13:48.195 --> 13:49.961
THAT STORY
ABOUT MY DAD'S TRUCK --

13:49.963 --> 13:51.629
I NEVER
ROLLED MY DAD'S TRUCK.

13:51.631 --> 13:52.997
THAT WAS JIMMY.

13:52.999 --> 13:54.999
TOOK IT OUT FOR A JOYRIDE,
FLIPS IT IN THE CREEK,

13:55.001 --> 13:56.201
ALMOST KILLED HIMSELF.

13:56.203 --> 13:57.535
HE COMES BACK,
HE'S SCARED TO DEATH

13:57.537 --> 13:59.037
OF WHAT MY DAD'S GONNA
DO TO HIM.

13:59.039 --> 14:00.705
SO YOU TOLD YOUR DAD
IT WAS YOU.
RIGHT.

14:00.707 --> 14:03.308
HE WAS 15. IT WOULD HAVE BEEN
FAR WORSE ON HIM, YOU KNOW?

14:03.310 --> 14:04.809
PLUS,
HE WAS DAD'S FAVORITE.

14:04.811 --> 14:06.010
JUST LIKE
EVE IS YOUR FAVORITE?

14:06.012 --> 14:07.445
<i>USED</i> TO BE.

14:07.447 --> 14:09.881
THE NEW RANKINGS
COME OUT TOMORROW.

14:16.489 --> 14:18.523
KRISTIN.
WHAT?

14:18.525 --> 14:20.959
BEEN RUNNING SOME PROJECTIONS
ON THIS RESTAURANT.

14:20.961 --> 14:22.460
I THINK
WE HAVE A PROBLEM.

14:22.462 --> 14:24.562
LET ME GUESS --
ANOTHER "WHAT IF?"

14:24.564 --> 14:27.899
LIKE "WHAT IF EVERYONE IN THE
WORLD BECOMES A VEGETARIAN?"

14:27.901 --> 14:30.668
I'D BE FINE WITH THAT.
I'M HEAVILY INVESTED IN SOY.

14:30.670 --> 14:34.572
BUT SERIOUSLY, THE COST
OF OPENING THIS PLACE IS HUGE.

14:34.574 --> 14:37.208
IF IT TANKS,
I'LL TAKE A BIG HIT.

14:37.210 --> 14:40.411
I'LL HAVE TO SELL
ONE OF MY DANCING HORSES.

14:40.413 --> 14:42.347
IT WON'T TANK.

14:42.349 --> 14:44.382
I PROMISE YOU,
IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.

14:44.384 --> 14:47.518
LOOK, 50% OF RESTAURANTS FAIL
IN THE FIRST THREE YEARS.

14:47.520 --> 14:50.021
I ONLY INVEST IN THINGS
I KNOW WILL SUCCEED.

14:50.023 --> 14:51.723
WAIT --
NO...ED, WAIT.

14:51.725 --> 14:55.026
Y-Y-YOU CAN'T GO INTO SOMETHING
WITH THAT KIND OF ATTITUDE.

14:55.028 --> 14:56.361
WHY NOT?

14:56.363 --> 14:57.996
FROM WHAT
YOU'VE BEEN TELLING ME,

14:57.998 --> 14:59.964
THAT'S THE ATTITUDE THAT
YOU'RE GOING INTO MARRIAGE WITH.

15:01.201 --> 15:03.067
VERY CLEVER.

15:04.771 --> 15:07.972
YES, "ALZATE" IS BASQUE
FOR "BRILLIANT."

15:09.242 --> 15:11.943
OR "FISHMONGER."
SOURCES VARY.

15:11.945 --> 15:15.013
YOU'VE BEEN ASKING ME
WHY MY MARRIAGES FAILED.

15:15.015 --> 15:16.581
I THINK THE BEST REASON

15:16.583 --> 15:19.017
IS THAT WHEN THINGS GOT HARD,
I STOPPED TRYING.

15:19.019 --> 15:20.518
I QUIT.

15:20.520 --> 15:22.086
WELL, I DON'T QUIT.

15:22.088 --> 15:24.923
I COMPLAIN LIKE HELL,
BUT I DON'T QUIT.

15:25.959 --> 15:28.426
THEN YOU HAVE
NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT.

15:28.428 --> 15:31.429
SO, I GUESS I'LL GIVE YOU
YOUR WEDDING PRESENT NOW.

15:31.431 --> 15:33.131
WHA--

15:33.133 --> 15:35.700
[ LAUGHS ]
A SUITE AT THE FOUR SEASONS?

15:35.702 --> 15:37.936
THIS IS SO GENEROUS!

15:39.606 --> 15:41.906
JUST, UH,
CHECK THE DATE.

15:41.908 --> 15:43.875
[ MUTTERS ]

15:43.877 --> 15:46.978
10 YEARS
FROM THE WEDDING.

15:48.081 --> 15:49.881
YEAH,
FOR YOUR ANNIVERSARY.

15:49.883 --> 15:53.084
LIKE I SAID, I ONLY INVEST IN
THINGS I KNOW WILL SUCCEED.

15:53.086 --> 15:55.954
THANK YOU.

15:55.956 --> 15:57.555
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:57.557 --> 15:59.958
I KNOW YOU AND BRIAN
WILL BE VERY HAPPY.

15:59.960 --> 16:01.259
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

16:01.261 --> 16:02.627
IT'S "RYAN."

16:03.930 --> 16:06.731
WELL, I GUESS IT MEANS
"FISHMONGER," THEN.

16:10.303 --> 16:12.937
OKAY. I JUST TOLD MANDY
WE WANT TO TALK TO HER.

16:12.939 --> 16:14.806
AND I ALSO CHECKED ON
YOUR DAD.

16:14.808 --> 16:18.609
HE FELL ASLEEP ON BOYD'S BED
WITH A HANDFUL OF TIES.

16:18.611 --> 16:20.578
WE COULD PLAY A GREAT TRICK
ON HIM RIGHT NOW --

16:20.580 --> 16:21.546
WE MOVE.

16:23.616 --> 16:25.149
WHY ARE WE DOING THIS
TO MANDY?

16:25.151 --> 16:26.951
THIS PARTY HAD
NOTHING TO DO WITH HER.

16:26.953 --> 16:28.619
THIS IS ALL ABOUT EVE.

16:28.621 --> 16:30.421
BUT MANDY LIED,
AND WE CAN'T LET THAT GO.

16:30.423 --> 16:32.090
WE JUST GOT TO SQUEEZE HER
A LITTLE

16:32.092 --> 16:33.958
AND GIVE HER A CHANCE
TO TO TELL THE TRUTH.

16:33.960 --> 16:35.460
SHE LIED
TO PROTECT HER SISTER.

16:35.462 --> 16:36.928
YEAH.

16:36.930 --> 16:40.131
MY SISTER NEVER
STUCK UP FOR ME.

16:40.133 --> 16:44.035
WELL...
WE ALL HATE APRIL.

16:44.037 --> 16:45.803
IS THIS
ABOUT MY PUNISHMENT?

16:45.805 --> 16:48.940
WELL, WE NEED A LITTLE MORE
INFORMATION FIRST.

16:48.942 --> 16:50.775
WHO DID YOU INVITE
TO THIS PARTY?

16:50.777 --> 16:54.312
UMM...JUST A COUPLE
OF FRIENDS FROM COLLEGE.

16:54.314 --> 16:55.780
MM,
AND WHAT SORT OF STUFF

16:55.782 --> 16:57.949
WERE YOU AND YOUR
COLLEGE FRIENDS GOING TO DO?

16:57.951 --> 16:59.617
MAYBE KARAOKE?

16:59.619 --> 17:01.986
[ Chuckling ]
YEAH, RIGHT.

17:01.988 --> 17:06.224
EVE'S FRIEND CAMMY SHOWED UP
HERE WITH A KARAOKE MACHINE.

17:06.226 --> 17:07.692
LOVE KARAOKE.
IT'S NOT LAME AT ALL.

17:07.694 --> 17:09.293
NEITHER IS CAMMY.
SHE'S NOT WEIRD.

17:10.530 --> 17:12.063
WE HAVE ENOUGH INFORMATION.

17:12.065 --> 17:15.500
ALL RIGHT, WELL, IT IS TIME
TO TELL YOU YOUR PUNISHMENT.

17:15.502 --> 17:17.835
OKAY, WHY -- WHY ARE WE
DOING THIS LIKE A GAME SHOW?

17:17.837 --> 17:20.838
[ Announcer voice ]
WE JUST WANT TO TELL YOU
WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO LOSE --

17:20.840 --> 17:25.176
A SPECTACULAR SPRING-BREAK TRIP
TO CANCúN, MéJICO.

17:25.178 --> 17:27.178
COME ON, GUYS.

17:27.180 --> 17:28.212
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

17:28.214 --> 17:29.547
YOU CAN'T DO THAT!

17:29.549 --> 17:31.516
YOU KNOW,
FROM WHAT YOU'VE TOLD US --

17:31.518 --> 17:33.985
OR<i> HAVEN'T</i> TOLD US --
YOU'VE LEFT US NO CHOICE.

17:34.888 --> 17:36.187
O-OKAY, FINE.
TAKE AWAY MY TRIP.

17:36.189 --> 17:37.688
ALL RIGHT, NO,
THAT'S NOT FAIR.

17:37.690 --> 17:38.890
SHUT UP, EVE.

17:38.892 --> 17:41.893
NO, YOU CAN'T DO THIS,
ALL RIGHT?

17:41.895 --> 17:43.694
IT WAS<i> MY</i> PARTY.
AHH.

17:43.696 --> 17:45.830
MANDY WAS JUST
COVERING FOR ME.

17:45.832 --> 17:47.665
SO, NOW WE HAVE THE TRUTH --
FROM THE RIGHT PERSON.

17:47.667 --> 17:49.033
MM-HMM.

17:49.035 --> 17:51.369
MANDY, I'M ACTUALLY
PROUD OF YOU.

17:51.371 --> 17:53.971
EVE, YOU'RE DEAD.

17:55.375 --> 17:56.874
YOU'RE PROUD OF ME
FOR LYING?

17:56.876 --> 17:58.576
AND YOU'RE MAD AT ME
FOR TELLING THE TRUTH?

17:58.578 --> 17:59.944
PARENTING IS COMPLICATED.

17:59.946 --> 18:01.345
CANCEL THE RUSSIAN BABY.

18:01.347 --> 18:02.780
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

18:02.782 --> 18:04.348
JIMMY.

18:04.350 --> 18:05.616
PROBABLY CAN'T FIND MY DAD.

18:05.618 --> 18:07.185
ARE YOU SURE
HE'S ASLEEP UPSTAIRS?

18:07.187 --> 18:09.720
YOU GET A MIRROR
UNDER HIS NOSE?
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

18:09.722 --> 18:10.788
YEAH.

18:10.790 --> 18:12.223
SURE, JIM. WHAT'S UP?

18:12.225 --> 18:13.858
MOM,
I'M REALLY SORRY.

18:13.860 --> 18:15.293
I KNOW WHAT I DID
WAS REALLY STUPID.
YEAH.

18:15.295 --> 18:16.761
I THINK
THAT WE'VE ALL LEARNED

18:16.763 --> 18:18.229
A VALUABLE LESSON
HERE TODAY --

18:18.231 --> 18:19.931
THAT I CAN STILL
GO TO CANCúN.

18:19.933 --> 18:22.033
NO, NO, NO,
HEY, GIRLS. LISTEN.

18:22.035 --> 18:24.135
OUR JOB AS PARENTS
IS TO PROTECT YOU.

18:24.137 --> 18:25.703
IF YOU'RE GONNA HIDE STUFF
FROM US,

18:25.705 --> 18:27.905
THEN SOMEBODY'S GOT TO STEP IN
AND ACT LIKE THE PARENT.

18:27.907 --> 18:29.874
NOW, COME ON -- PART OF
HAVING EACH OTHER'S BACKS

18:29.876 --> 18:32.110
IS TO MAKE SURE YOUR SISTER
DOESN'T DO SOMETHING STUPID.

18:32.112 --> 18:33.144
YES.
I UNDERSTAND.

18:33.146 --> 18:34.078
YEAH.
YEAH?

18:34.080 --> 18:34.912
OKAY. GOT IT.

18:34.914 --> 18:36.447
GOOD.

18:42.489 --> 18:43.821
WE SHOULD HAVE
BLAMED KRISTIN.

18:43.823 --> 18:45.189
OH, THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN
SO GOOD!

18:47.260 --> 18:50.094
YEAH. THAT'S GREAT, JIMMY.
YOU NEVER FAIL TO DISAPPOINT.

18:50.096 --> 18:51.729
WHAT'S GOING ON?

18:53.399 --> 18:54.765
JIMMY CAN'T MAKE DINNER
WITH MY DAD

18:54.767 --> 18:56.234
BECAUSE HE'S
IN A "BUSINESS MEETING."

18:56.236 --> 18:57.401
[ SCOFFS ]

18:57.403 --> 18:58.669
THE KIND OF MEETING
THAT HAS

18:58.671 --> 18:59.770
A GIRL GIGGLING
IN THE BACKGROUND.

18:59.772 --> 19:01.072
OH, GOD.

19:01.074 --> 19:02.673
HE WANTS YOU TO MAKE
AN EXCUSE TO YOUR DAD.

19:02.675 --> 19:04.509
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M NOT LYING FOR HIM THIS TIME.

19:04.511 --> 19:06.077
YEAH. YOU SHOULD JUST
GET MANDY TO DO IT.

19:06.079 --> 19:07.411
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:07.413 --> 19:08.679
I TOLD HIM
TO JUST MAKE THE DINNER

19:08.681 --> 19:09.947
OR I'LL KICK HIS ASS.

19:09.949 --> 19:11.182
THAT'S ALL
I COULD COME UP WITH.

19:11.184 --> 19:13.017
YEAH? YOU THINK
THAT'S GONNA WORK?

19:13.019 --> 19:14.452
HE'S A LOT BIGGER AND STRONGER.
I MAY NEED YOU TO TAG IN.

19:14.454 --> 19:15.953
GOT IT.

19:15.955 --> 19:17.021
SORRY TO HEAR IT.

19:17.023 --> 19:18.256
NO, IT'S ALL RIGHT,
JIMMY.

19:18.258 --> 19:19.123
DON'T WORRY A BIT
ABOUT IT.

19:19.125 --> 19:21.292
IT'S OKAY.

19:21.294 --> 19:24.195
WELL, JIMMY GOT HELD UP
IN A BUSINESS MEETING.

19:24.197 --> 19:25.429
[ SCOFFS ]

19:25.431 --> 19:27.131
HE'S GOT A LOT OF IRONS
IN THE FIRE.

19:27.133 --> 19:28.866
EVERYBODY WANTS
A PIECE OF THAT KID.

19:28.868 --> 19:31.769
WELL, THEY'RE GONNA HAVE TO
WAIT IN LINE, DAD.

19:31.771 --> 19:32.870
I'M SORRY, BUD.

19:32.872 --> 19:34.372
YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE WELCOME TO STAY

19:34.374 --> 19:36.140
AND CELEBRATE OUR ANNIVERSARY
WITH US.

19:36.142 --> 19:37.542
NO.
HE'S JUST RUNNING LATE.

19:37.544 --> 19:39.443
HE SAID HE WOULD
DEFINITELY BE THERE.

19:39.445 --> 19:41.212
AND IT SEEMED
VERY IMPORTANT TO HIM

19:41.214 --> 19:42.513
THAT I LET YOU KNOW THAT.

19:43.683 --> 19:45.683
JIMMY'S A...GOOD SON.

19:45.685 --> 19:48.052
BUD, THE ONLY REASON
HE'S COMING IS BECAUSE --

19:48.054 --> 19:49.453
BECAUSE HE'S A PRINCE.

19:49.455 --> 19:51.322
ALWAYS HAS BEEN, DAD.
HE'S A GOOD KID.

19:51.324 --> 19:52.957
YEAH.
BUT WHAT ABOUT YOU?

19:52.959 --> 19:55.526
YOU GOT A WHOLE RACK OF TIES
UP THERE, MIKE.

19:55.528 --> 19:58.796
SPENDING A LOT OF TIME
IN COURT?

19:58.798 --> 20:00.131
I'M GONNA NEED THAT TIE
BACK, DAD.

20:00.133 --> 20:01.699
IT'S MY LUCKY FUNERAL TIE.

20:01.701 --> 20:04.502
EVERY TIME I WEAR THAT,
I'M NOT THE DEAD GUY.

20:12.212 --> 20:14.245
HEY. MIKE BAXTER HERE
FOR OUTDOOR MAN.

20:14.247 --> 20:16.214
WHAT'S THE BEST WAY
TO RUN A FAMILY?

20:16.216 --> 20:18.182
WE ALL AGREE
THAT LETTING PEOPLE VOTE

20:18.184 --> 20:20.051
IS THE BEST WAY
TO RUN A COUNTRY.

20:20.053 --> 20:23.254
WELL, YOU DO GET SOME PUSHBACK
FROM THE DICTATORS OUT THERE --

20:23.256 --> 20:27.592
KIM JONG-UN,
THE CASTRO BROTHERS, OBAMA.

20:27.594 --> 20:30.561
BEING A DICTATOR
IS NO WAY TO RUN A COUNTRY.

20:30.563 --> 20:32.897
BUT, GOSH DARN IT, IT'S
THE ONLY WAY TO RUN A FAMILY.

20:32.899 --> 20:34.599
YOU KNOW,
IT WORKS FOR MAFIA FAMILIES.

20:34.601 --> 20:36.400
IN THOSE FAMILIES
YOU NEVER HEAR,

20:36.402 --> 20:40.538
"LOOK, ALL IN FAVOR OF WHACKING
JOHNNY ROAST BEEF, SAY AYE."

20:40.540 --> 20:41.872
WHEN YOUR KIDS ARE LITTLE,

20:41.874 --> 20:43.574
YOU CAN'T GIVE THEM
A LOT OF FREEDOM.

20:43.576 --> 20:45.243
THEY DON'T HAVE
THE INALIENABLE RIGHT

20:45.245 --> 20:46.777
TO STICK A FORK
IN A WALL SOCKET.

20:46.779 --> 20:48.779
BEING A PARENT
IS LIKE BEING A KING,

20:48.781 --> 20:52.216
EXCEPT YOUR SUBJECTS ARE GETTING
BIGGER AND SMARTER ALL THE TIME.

20:52.218 --> 20:54.385
SO YOU GOT TO STAY
ONE STEP AHEAD OF THEM.

20:54.387 --> 20:55.853
ONE TRICK DICTATORS USE

20:55.855 --> 20:57.521
IS TO TURN THEIR SUBJECTS
AGAINST EACH OTHER,

20:57.523 --> 20:59.690
WHICH IS TEMPTING
TO DO WITH YOUR KIDS, RIGHT?

20:59.692 --> 21:01.259
BUT, LIKE COCKFIGHTING,

21:01.261 --> 21:02.960
IT'S FUN TO WATCH,
BUT ULTIMATELY KIND OF WRONG.

21:02.962 --> 21:04.228
[<i> CLUCKING</i> ]

21:04.230 --> 21:06.097
IDEALLY,
YOU WANT YOUR KIDS TO BE CLOSE

21:06.099 --> 21:07.398
SO THAT
WHEN YOU'RE NO LONGER AROUND,

21:07.400 --> 21:08.866
THEY HAVE EACH OTHER.

21:08.868 --> 21:11.969
AS THE WRITER
JEAN BAPTISTE LEGOUVé SAID,

21:11.971 --> 21:16.073
"A SIBLING
IS A FRIEND GIVEN BY NATURE."

21:16.075 --> 21:18.042
WHICH TELLS ME
FRENCHY WEIRD NAME

21:18.044 --> 21:20.811
NEVER GOT JAMMED INTO
A CLOTHES DRYER BY HIS BROTHER.

21:20.813 --> 21:23.814
SO, IN CLOSING,
I WANT TO MAKE AMENDS

21:23.816 --> 21:25.283
AND SAY "SORRY"
TO MY YOUNGER BROTHER, JIMMY.

21:25.285 --> 21:26.651
BUT AT LEAST WHEN YOU CAME OUT,

21:26.653 --> 21:28.819
YOU WERE FLUFFY
AND SPRINGTIME-FRESH.
